data.enText: to force sb to do sth; to make sth necessary

data.chText: 这项法律可强制父亲定期支付子女的费用。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: The law can compel fathers to make regular payments for their children.

data.chText: 我觉得必须写信告诉你我是多么欣赏你的书。
data.enText: I feel compelled to write and tell you how much I enjoyed your book.

data.chText: 去年他因身体不好被迫退休了。
data.enText: Last year ill health compelled his retirement.

before.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.chText: 他用权威的口气讲话，引起了整个人群的注意。
data.enText: He spoke with an authority that compelled the attention of the whole crowd.

simple_means.memory_skill: com 表加强 + pel 驱动，推 → 一再推 → 强迫

ex.chText: 地主迫使农奴们每天干活16个小时。
ex.enText: The landlord forced the serfs to work 16 hours a day.
The manager was forced to resign.

ex.chText: 背部受伤使她不得不退出比赛。
ex.enText: She was forced to withdraw from the game because of a back injury.

ex.chText: 基利强迫我告诉他真相。
ex.enText: Keally forced me to tell him the truth.
She forced herself to get out of bed.

synonyms.bx: 指通过威胁等迫使他人做不愿做的事情，或指局势、事件等使某人必须做某事。

ex.chText: 这项法律可强迫雇主提供养老保险。
ex.enText: The law can compel employers to provide endowment insurance.

ex.chText: 恶劣的天气迫使他们呆在家里。
ex.enText: Bad weather compelled them to stay at home.

ex.chText: 她觉得必须打电话告诉他她是多么欣赏他的音乐。
ex.enText: She felt compelled to call and tell him how much she enjoyed his music.

ex.chText: 下雨使我们不得不放弃那项计划。
ex.enText: The rain compelled us to cancel the plan.

synonyms.bx: 多指人、局势、规定等迫使某人做某事；也指觉得必须去做某事，常因为这么做是正确的。

example: We compel all students to fill out this form

value.def: If a situation, a rule, or a person compels you to do something, they force you to do it.

example.ex: ...the introduction of legislation to compel cyclists to wear a helmet...
example.tran: 强制骑自行车者戴头盔的法律的出台

example.ex: Leonie's mother was compelled to take in washing to help support her family...
example.tran: 利奥妮的妈妈被迫在家替人洗衣服，以贴补家用。

example.ex: Local housing authorities have been compelled by the housing crisis to make offers of sub-standard accommodation.
example.tran: 住房危机迫使当地的几个房管部门提供不够标准的住房。

value.def: If you feel compelled to do something, you feel that you must do it, because it is the right thing to do.

example.ex: Dickens felt compelled to return to the stage for a final good-bye...
example.tran: 迪肯斯觉得必须返回舞台作最后的道别。

example.ex: I felt morally compelled to help.
example.tran: 我觉得从道义上我必须帮忙。
